title: doma_umaru
body:
Main character of [[Himouto! Umaru-chan]].

A popular high school girl, but at home she becomes [[komaru (himouto! umaru-chan)|a spoiled chibi otaku]] and also visits the local gaming hall under the guise of [[UMR (himouto! umaru-chan)|]], her screen name in the [[arcade]] game high score lists. She lives with her older brother [[Doma Taihei|Taihei]]. 

She has [[very long hair|very long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[brown eyes]].

title: motoba_kirie
body:
Classmate of [[Doma Umaru]] and younger sister of [[Motoba Takeshi]] in [[Himouto! Umaru-chan]]. She has dark purple hair that is often tied in a [[ponytail]]. She also has dark purple eyes. 

At school, she is described as having an extremely menacing aura, which led to her having few friends. She was once seen beating up her older brother. Because of these things, other students at school became afraid to approach her or get to know her. In truth, she is actually quite shy and it is implied that she is only able to talk to small children. 

After befriending [[Komaru (himouto! umaru-chan)|]], she gradually becomes more social, open and confidant.

title: kamijou_touma
body:
A character from [[Toaru Majutsu no Index]].
He is the main protagonist of the [[Toaru Majutsu no Index]] series and an important character in the [[Toaru Kagaku no Railgun]] series. As a Level 0 Academy City first-year high school student, his point-of-view allows the audience to become acquainted to the mysterious world of Toaru Majutsu no Index, and is mostly involved in the events of its Magic Side.
He possesses the mysterious [[Imagine Breaker]] in his right hand, which is capable of negating all forms of magic, esper powers, and other divine abilities. This, according to [[Index (toaru majutsu no index)|]], even includes his own good luck, as they are the blessings of God.

He has a very strong desire to aid all those who are in need even if it means putting his life on the line and will not hesitate to challenge an opponent who is several times more powerful than himself. Because of his willingness to help others unconditionally, he has attracted the affections of many characters in the series, which Himegami Aisa jokes about, stating that his life is like a dating simulation where he is bound to unlock more paths to more girls

h4. See also

* [[SoGeBu (meme)|]] - A meme involving his signature catchphrase.

title: virtual_on
body:
[i][b]Cyber Troopers Virtual-ON[/b][/i], or simply [i]Virtual-ON[/i], is a fast-paced, 3D [[mecha]] fighting game created by [[Sega]]. Many of the series' mechas were designed by Hajime Katoki, one of the mecha designers of the [[Gundam]] franchise. The game puts players in 3D arena where they take control of giant mechas known as Virtuaroids to defeat the other player. When it first debuted in arcades, it used a unique twin-stick set-up to give the players the idea of piloting a giant mecha. The series has seen three sequels and ports on video game consoles. 

Some of the Virtuaroids such Temjin and Fei-Yen have featured in a few games in the [i][[Super Robot Wars]][/i] series; Fei-Yen also been crossed-over with [[Vocaloid]]'s [[Hatsune Miku]] as Fei-Yen HD in [i]Super Robot Wars UX[/i]. In addition, the franchise collaborated with [i][[Toaru Majutsu no Index]][/i] in [i][[Toaru Majutsu no Virtual-On]][/i].

title: jizou
body: A divinity in Japanese Buddhism most commonly known for being the patron of children, expectant mothers, travelers and pilgrims, firemen, and guardian of children in limbo. The localized version of Ksitigarbha, he is one of the most popular bodhisattva ([i]bosatsu[/i] in Japanese--a person who attains enlightenment but postpones becoming a Buddha in order to help others) of the 16 attendants of Amida Buddha, a savior par exellence of those in need. Statues of male Jizou as a bald monk, standing with one foot slightly forward, with a staff in his right hand to push open the gates of Hell and a pearl or gem in his left to light the darkness, are found in cemeteries and along roadsides, ostensibly to invoke his help and protection.

title: harries_technique
body:
A method of holding a [[handgun]] and a [[flashlight]] simultaneously while keeping the gun steady and the flashlight pointed in the same direction, developed by Michael Harries, a shooting instructor and retired US Marine.

"[T]he flashlight is maintained in an "ice pick" grip while the handgun is thrust forward, at which point the non-shooting hand crosses beneath the handgun-retaining arm. The technique finishes with the backs of the hands against one another, creating isometric tension for stability." ("Source":http://www.iwillnotbeavictim.com/flashlight_hold-page.html)

Examples can be seen "here":http://www.theboxotruth.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/22.jpg, "here":http://www.iwillnotbeavictim.com/sitebuilder/images/jsw_hb_7-291x188.jpg, and "here":http://www.iwillnotbeavictim.com/sitebuilder/images/jsw_hb_6-287x185.jpg.

title: alex_(street_fighter)
body:
[b]Alex[/b] ([b]アレックス[/b]) is a character in the [[Street Fighter]] series. He first appeared in and is the protagonist of [[Street Fighter III (series)|Street Fighter III]].

He hasn't been with his parents since he was a little kid, and his current family consists of his father's friend Tom and Tom's teenage daughter Patricia, all three of them living under the same roof. Alex trains daily at Tom's gym, and Tom being a military veteran and a renowned refiner of fighting moves often visits military bases as well as maintaining his own gym. Alex entered the third World Warrior tournament because its sponsor, [[Gill (street fighter)|]], had seriously injured his best friend and mentor/father figure Tom, even though Tom had told him Gill had won fairly. Tom allowed him to go, letting him make his own decision. Alex won every match and then faced Gill. Although he defeated Gill, Alex did not have a chance to kill him, and he went home, to find Tom fully recovered.

title: warlic
body:
[b]Warlic[/b], also known as [b]the Blue Mage[/b] is a character that is part of the [[artix_entertainment|Artix Entertainment]] universe. He is considered the most powerful wielder of magic in all of Lore. He is a recurrent character in [[dragonfable|DragonFable]], where he was once killed by Nythera, his apprentice, but he laters come back; he helps The Hero many times throughout the game. In [[adventurequest_worlds|AdventureQuest Worlds]] he owns a magic shop in Battleon Town, where he sells a lot of things; he's also a major character during the [b]13 Lords of Chaos saga[/b]. He also appears in [[adventurequest|AdventureQuest]].

[spoiler]It is later revealed that he was actually an infernal but he didn't desire destruction like the others. He then rebelled against his father, pushing him off a cliff and thus, he was descended from his original state to a Human/Infernal hybrid.[/spoiler]

title: help:text_syntax
body:
When searching by text, the following variation in search parameters may be used.

h5. Direct comparisons

These take the text field in its entirety when making the comparison as selected by the qualifier. The following qualifiers are available.

* (No qualifier) - Direct equality comparison.
* [code]*_eq[/code] - Same as above.
* [code]*_not_eq[/code] - Direct inequality comparison.
* [code]*_like[/code] - Equality comparison, supports the wildcard "*".
* [code]*_ilike[/code] - Same as above, though with case-insensitivity.
* [code]*_not_like[/code] - Inequality comparison, supports the wildcard "*".
* [code]*_not_ilike[/code] - Same as above, though with case-insensitivity.
* [code]*_regex[/code] - Regex equality comparison, follows Postgres' ERE regex formatting rules.
* [code]*_not_regex[/code] - Regex inequality comparison, follows Postgres' ERE regex formatting rules.

h5. Array comparisons

These break up the text field allowing multiple comparisons at once, either using the URL array format or a certain text separator. The following qualifiers are available.

* [code]*_array[/code] - Uses the URL array format making direct equality comparisons.
** Example: [code]search[name_array][]=foo&search[name_array][]=bar[/code]
* [code]*_comma[/code] - Uses a comma to break up the text field.
* [code]*_space[/code] - Uses a space to break up the text field.

[b]Note:[/b] A lowercase transformation will be applied on both sides of the equality comparison on search parameters that use the "lower" qualifier, e.g. [code]search[name_lower_comma]=Foo,Bar[/code]

h5. All parameter variations

For the following, [code]NAME[/code] is the name of the record field being searched for.

* [code]NAME[/code]
* [code]NAME_eq[/code]
* [code]NAME_not_eq[/code]
* [code]NAME_like[/code]
* [code]NAME_not_like[/code]
* [code]NAME_ilike[/code]
* [code]NAME_not_ilike[/code]
* [code]NAME_regex[/code]
* [code]NAME_not_regex[/code]
* [code]NAME_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_comma[/code]
* [code]NAME_space[/code]
* [code]NAME_lower_array[/code]
* [code]NAME_lower_comma[/code]
* [code]NAME_lower_space[/code]

h4. See also

* [[Help:Number syntax]]
* [[Help:Array syntax]]
* [[Help:API]]

h4. Trivia

* In the transition from [[defense_of_the_ancients|DotA]] to [[Dota 2]], various aspects of [b]Mirana[/b]'s character have been changed to avoid reference to Blizzard intellectual property.
** The names of two of Mirana's abilities were changed; Starstorm was previously called Starfall and Sacred Arrow was called Elune's Arrow.
** Her [[defense_of_the_ancients|DotA]] hero title was "[b]Priestess of the Moon[/b]", a class within the [[Warcraft]] universe. Her title was changed during the beta to her current, [b]Princess of the Moon[/b]. However, her voice lines remained unchanged, referring to herself still as the Priestess.
* In addition to the above changes, [b]Mirana[/b]'s surname - "[b]Nightshade[/b]" - was also dropped, so that she is known simply as "[b]Mirana[/b]".
* [b]Mirana[/b] is the tiger of the Multan Fort that killed the king of Mongols (in the Mongol folklore).
* Her mount's name is Sagan. Her response "Carl meet Sagan." is a pun on [b]Carl Sagan[/b].
* She appears to be wearing the Circlet item, which fits the item description as being "designed for human princesses".

title: chagama_(pot)
body:
A chagama is a metal [[pot]] or [[kettle]] used in the Japanese [[tea ceremony]] to heat the water for the tea.  It is a cast iron pot with a lid and a lug on each side for the handles to be attached.  They may be depicted with a portable brazier called a [i]furo[/i], which features an opening at the top for the chagama to be set in above the flames and would feature an opening on the side to monitor the flame as well as provide air.

The chagama does not feature a spout and instead a [[hishaku|ladle]] is used to draw water from it.

title: charging_bull
body:
[i]Charging Bull[/i] is a bronze sculpture by Italian-American sculptor Arturo Di Modica that stands on Broadway just north of Bowling Green in the Financial District of Manhattan in New York City. The bronze sculpture stands 11 feet (3.4 m) tall, 16 feet (4.9 m) long, and weighs 7,100-pounds (3,200 kg).  The sculpture is supposed to represent the "bull" (rising) market and thriving economy.

On March 7, 2017 the bronze sculpture [i][[Fearless Girl]][/i] was installed facing down [i]Charging Bull[/i].  It was later moved in 2018 after complaints from Arturo Di Modica.

title: starfleet_uniform
body:
A uniform from Starfleet, from the [[Star Trek]] universe. There are actually variations per series/film in the franchise.

h5. [i]The Original Series[/i] (includes the Mirror Universe)
[tn]See post #4633403, left side.[/tn]

In the TOS, set in the 2250s to the early 2270s, the standard duty uniform consists of a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[tunic]] with rank insignia sleeve stripes, color-coded by division (gold = command, red = operations, blue = sciences/medics), black [[undershirt]]s, black pants, and black [[boots]]. Captains wore a green-yellow wraparound tunic similar to East Asian clothing. Female uniforms were of a single tunic/[[miniskirt]] combo with [[pantyhose]].

[tn]See post #5449483 for Mirror Universe.[/tn]

In the episode [i]Mirror, Mirror[/i], the Terran Empire uniform is similar, replacing the Starfleet delta insignia with the sword-and-globe imperial insignia and adding a gold [[sash]] belt. Female uniforms consisted of a [[tank top]], black [[midriff]] undershirt, [[miniskirt]], and [[thighhighs|thighhigh]] boots.

h5. [i]The Next Generation[/i]
[tn]See post #1121461.[/tn]

The TNG, set in the 2350s, has a different version of the uniform: a black [[jumpsuit]] with the assigned color of division in front (red = command, gold = operations, blue = sciences), Starfleet insignia on the left breast side, rank insignia on the right [[collar]].

h5. J.J. Abrams' [i]Kelvin Timeline[/i] films
[tn]See post #4633403, right side.[/tn]

Similar to the TOS but updated to have solid rank sleeve stripes and darker color shades.

h4. External links
* "Memory Alpha/Star Trek Wikia article":[https://memory-alpha.fandom.com/wiki/Starfleet_uniform]

title: agano_(cruiser)
body:
"Agano":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_cruiser_Agano is the lead ship of the [i]Agano[/i]-class light cruisers.  Completed in October 31st of 1942, and was sunk by the submarine [i]USS Skate[/i] on February 16th 1944 while heading to Japan from Truk to receive repairs from damage in the Solomons campaign.  

They were among the last light cruisers the IJN ever developed, and were heavier than most light cruisers, but were consequently under-armed and under-armored for their weight, as the IJN did not increase those capabilities as much as the mass.  The Agano class was characteristic for having only a single [[smokestack]], as the light cruiser design was re-evaluated to have less clutter on the decks, be less overweight for its hull, and hence, have better stability in open seas.

In real life, Agano and her sisters were to have replaced the aging [i]Tenryuu[/i], [i]Kuma[/i], and [i]Nagara[/i] classes of light cruisers as destroyer squadron and submarine squadron flagships. Only her sisters Noshiro and Yahagi were able to fulfill that said role, however.
She was completed in mid-1942 and thrown into the front lines of the Guadalcanal and Solomons campaigns, eventually seeing action in the battle of Empress Augusta Bay on 2 November 1943. Just a few days later, she sustained severe damage from an air attack by US carriers and was forced to withdraw to Truk.

Not fully repaired, she was again attacked by US naval forces in Truk on February 1944 and sunk while retreating to Japan, with the destroyer Oite rescuing more than 500 survivors. The next day, Oite herself was sunk with all of the Agano survivors.

The [[garter toss]] is the counterpart tradition for the groom and bachelors attending.

title: garter_toss
body: A western [[wedding]] tradition which involves two parts.  During the first part the [[bride]] sits on a chair and the [[groom]] then goes under her skirt to remove one of her garters either by hand or by tradition with his teeth.  The second part is the garter toss, where the garter is then tossed to the bachelors attending the wedding.  The bachelor who catches the garter is said to be the next person who'd become wed.  The garter toss is the counterpart to the bride's [[bouquet toss]].
